24 'Sec. 14. 28-B MRSA §512, sub-§1, as amended by PL 2023, c. 679, Pt. B, §110,
25 is further amended to read:
26 1. Inspections. A licensee shall submit to an inspection of its licensed premises,
27 including, but not limited to, any places of storage and any locked areas, upon demand and
28 without notice during the licensee's business hours by the office, a criminal justice agency
29 or an official authorized by the municipality in which the licensed premises are located.
30 Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, a law enforcement officer may enter
31 any part of a licensed premises that is not open to the public only when:
32 A. The licensee voluntarily allows the law enforcement officer to enter the part of the
33 premises that is not open to the public;
34 B. The law enforcement officer's entry is authorized pursuant to a warrant issued by a
35 duly authorized justice, judge or justice of the peace; or
